               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i0">
                     <locus from="1r" to="27v">1r-27v</locus>
                     <textLang xml:lang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                     <title type="acephalous" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT0049IHA#s36IHA">قران, Twenty ninth ǧuz’ (29/30)</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar">
                        <locus target="#1r">-1r</locus>عسَىٰ رَبُّنَا أَن يُبْدِلَنَا خَيْرًا مِّنْهَا إِنَّا إِلَىٰ رَبِّنَا رَاغِبُونَ<note>68:32</note>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar">
                        <locus target="#27v">-27v</locus>سورة المرسلات مكية وهي خمسون ايوة . بِسْمِ اللّهِ الرَّحْمنِ الرَّحِيمِ وَالْمُرْسَلَاتِ عُرْفًا فَالْعَاصِفَاتِ عَصْفًا وَالنَّاشِرَاتِ نَشْرًا  فَالْفَارِقَاتِ فَرْقًا  فَالْمُ<note>72:1</note>
                     </explicit>
                     <note>68:32-72:1. Some words are divided into two different lines.
The “ḏāl” is written with the dot inside. Sometimes the catchword is only the first part of the first word in the next page, sometimes there is a repeated word and the catchword is the second word of the next page. 
The name of the scribe appears in mss. 4521D (37r) and 4521X (1v, 45v). The note stating that he is actually the scribe is in 4521X (45v).  </note>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
